A decade ago my parents spent all of their life savings so that we can come to America in the pursuit of the American Dream and to have a better chance at life. Ten years ago you stepped on this foreign land not even knowing how to say basic words in english. Today you are the first one in the family to graduate college and  and is now a Lieutenant in the U.S Army. 
Some guy with overly nappy dreads once told me that not all of us was meant to succeed. You are part of the minority. You are meant to succeed.
